HEAT oven to 375 degrees F. Grease a 11/2-quart baking dish or 9-inch pie plate with butter or non-stick cooking spray. COOK sausage in skillet over medium-high heat, stirring for 3 to 4 minutes or until sausage is no longer pink. Drain excess fat. Add celery, onion and cranberries. Continue cooking and stir occasionally for 3 to 4 minutes or until onions are soft. Remove from heat. STIR in bread cubes, apple juice and butter; mix well. Spoon into baking dish or pie plate; cover with lid or aluminum foil. BAKE for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot throughout. Serve as is or use to stuff a 10- to 12-lb. turkey.